From Dan Hardiker in email:

A way of intercepting the page during rendering and altering it ourselves before rendering continues would be great - we can botch this already by creating a component plugin which defines a rendering component and overrides the internal one - however this is very ugly and suffers race conditions (what if 2 plugins attempt this?). A use case would be to search and replace for keywords (perhaps just the first occurance) and wrap them with a div layer which pops up their definition.

