It would be really nice if you could click on the header bar (herin "task bar") of a {dynamictasklist} and have the tasks and add box show/hide - basically allowing you to wrap up the list so you can only see the task bar or have the list displayed so you can see the task bar and all the items + add box.

A new param of wrapped=true would set the default state.

I want this feature because I have several pages with herds of task lists on them (just general to-do lists, not stuff I'd want to manage with Jira) and as such it would be great to open that page and just see the task bars (basically a summary of each list) and then be able to click on them to see and alter the tasks.

